               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; the names of the Trinity; the name Ṗäraqliṭos and the
                        name of other protagonists; the name of the donors.&#xD; A few lines
                        alternating with black lines in the incipit page of Text I; incipit of Text
                        II and of each miracle; the initial words of some paragraphs in Texts I and
                        II; some interlineal corrections (e.g., fol. 12rb).&#xD; Elements of the
                        punctuation signs and Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- In this Ms., miracle 3 has been divided into two independent miracles:
                        the first part (in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESap046">AP-046</ref>= miracle 3,
                        fols. 53ra-56ra l.11) and miracle 4 with the second part (in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESap046">AP-046</ref>= miracle 3, fols. 56ra l.11-59ra-l.3). As
                        a consequence, the total number of the miracles is 12; they are not
                        numbered.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="30vb"/>Fol. 30vb: ተፈጸመት፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ አመ፴ሁ፡ ለጥር፡
                        በ፲፱፸፱ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ በዘመነ፡ ሉቃስ፡ ዘወሀባ፡ ለታቦተ፡ ጰራቅሊጦስ፡ አቶ፡ ጰራቅሊጦ[ስ]፡ ኃይለ፡ ሥላሴ፡
                        ወብእሲቱ፡ [vac] ከመ፡ ይኩኖሙ፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>The note states that the Ms. was completed on the 30th of Ṭǝrr in the
                           year of mercy 1979, during the time of the Evangelist Luke (= 25 January
                           1986/87 A.D.). Besides, it is said that ʾato Ṗäraqliṭos Ḫaylä Śǝllase (?)
                           donated it to the tabot of the church, together with his wife, whose name
                           however is missing.</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
